<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Continues U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Continues U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets U.S. Treasury Secretary 2 May </H4>

<F P=102> OW0305124994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0652 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0305124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Ying Qian (2019 6197)] </F>
  [Text] Washington, 2 May (XINHUA) -- In meeting with Zou 
Jiahua, visiting vice premier of the Chinese State Council, on 
the afternoon of 2 May in Washington, U.S. Treasury Secretary 
Lloyd Bentsen said there are many points in common between the 
United States and China and hoped the two countries could 
establish long-term and constructive relations of friendship and 
cooperation. 
  Lloyd Bentsen welcomed Zou Jiahua's visit. He happily 
recalled his visit to China not long ago and said he saw great 
changes taking place in China and he gained a lot from the visit. 
  Lloyd Bentsen held that the United States and China should 
expand cooperation in various fields because it is not only in 
accord with the basic interests of the people of the two 
countries but also conducive to peace and development in the 
Asia-Pacific region and the world. 
  Zou Jiahua pointed out that the current level of relations 
between China and the United States are the result of joint 
efforts of the two countries. The two sides should cherish such 
relations. He said: Since the Sino-U.S. summit in Seattle last 
November, exchanges and cooperation between the two countries in 
various fields have made headway. However, the two sides should 
continue their efforts to further improve and develop relations 
between the two countries. 
  Zou Jiahua hoped both China and the United States would, 
based on the fundamental interests of the people of the two 
countries, gradually overcome their differences at present 
through negotiations, set their eyes on the future, and promote 
the healthy development of relations between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

