<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren Meets U.S. Guests; Discusses U.S. Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rong Yiren Meets U.S. Guests; Discusses U.S. Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0405063594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0625 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0405063594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 4 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-President 
Rong Yiren expressed the hope here today that Sino-U.S. ties 
would be further improved and developed. 
  He told Frank Zarb, vice-chairman and executive officer of 
the Travelers Company of the United States, during their meeting 
that since the two countries play important roles in the world, 
the improvement and development of their bilateral ties would 
not only serve the interests of the two peoples, but also 
benefit peace and development in the world. 
  He hoped that the existing differences should not damage 
normal political and economic exchanges between the two 
countries, and that the differences could be solved through 
discussions and exchanges. 
  He said that the meeting between Chinese President Jiang 
Zemin and U.S. President Clinton in Seattle last year was 
beneficial to the improvement of bilateral relations, and he 
hoped that the favorable tendency of development could be 
maintained. 
  Zarb agreed with Rong's views and said that in the United 
States many people now enthusiastically hope that U.S.-China 
relations will improve. 
  Zarb and his party are here as guests of the China 
International Trust and Investment Company. 
  The Travelers Company is one of the largest insurance 
companies in the United States, with total assets valued at over 
101.3 billion U.S. dollars, and the turnover in 1993 stood at 
6.8 billion U.S. dollars. 

</TEXT>

