<H3> <TI>   Chinese, Uzbekistan Trade Union Leaders Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese, Uzbekistan Trade Union Leaders Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0205151594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1426 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0205151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 2 (XINHUA) -- Wei Jianxing, president 
of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions, met with a 
delegation from the Federation of Trade Unions of Uzbekistan led 
by its council Chairman Hulkar Djamalov here this evening. 
  Wei, also member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese 
Communist Party Central Committee, said that Chinese Premier Li 
Peng's visit to Uzbekistan not long ago was a great success and 
brought bilateral ties to a new stage of development. 
  He said with certainty that the delegation's visit will help 
deepen mutual understanding and friendship between the two trade 
union federations. 
  During the meeting Wei also briefed the visitors on China's 
economic growth, measures that China has taken in curbing 
inflation and tasks that the Chinese trade unions are confronted 
with under the new situation. 
  After the meeting, Wei hosted a dinner in honor of the 
delegation, which arrived here on April 30. 

</TEXT>

