<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihan Continues Visit to Finland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihan Continues Visit to Finland </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Prime Minister 4 May </H4>

<F P=102> OW0405100394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0925 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0405100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Helsinki, May 4 (XINHUA) -- Finnish Prime Minister 
Esko Aho today met with Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National 
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference (CPPCC), to discuss ways of furthering friendly 
relations between the two countries. 
  Li, who arrived here Monday [2 May] for a goodwill official 
visit at the invitation of the Finnish Government, said that 
China and Finland, with a traditional friendship, have been 
enjoying sound relations despite the changing international 
situation. 
  He praised the Sino-Finnish relationship as a model of 
friendly cooperation between nations with different social 
systems. 
  The CPPCC chairman attributed the successful Sino-Finnish 
relations to mutual respect, frequent exchanges, cooperation 
based on equality and mutual benefit, and consultations aimed at 
seeking common ground while reserving differences. 
  Li said the two countries have tremendous potential for 
mutual cooperation because China is a developing country 
adopting a policy of reform and opening to the outside world 
while Finland is a developed industrial nation. 
  He hoped that relations between the two countries will be 
enhanced to a new level on the current basis. 
  Prime Minister Aho, who has visited China recently, was glad 
to meet with Li again and described his recent trip to China as 
a great success. 
  Aho was satisfied with the development of relations between 
the two countries, saying that Finland and China have succeeded 
in developing their friendly cooperation in all fields since 
they forged diplomatic ties. 
  Especially in recent years, he said, economic, trade and 
scientific and technological cooperation between the two 
countries has been boosted greatly. 
  Through a repeated exchange of visits, he said, both 
countries have also found a lot of common ground and reached 
understanding on many issues. 
  Helsinki is the first leg of Li's five-European-nation tour 
which will also take him to Sweden, Norway, Denmark and Belgium. 
  This is the first time for China's CPPCC chairman to visit 
these countries. 

</TEXT>

