<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihan Continues Visit to Finland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihan Continues Visit to Finland </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Foreign Minister </H4>

<F P=102> OW0405102894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0917 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0405102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Helsinki, May 4 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), and Finnish Foreign Minister 
Heikki Haavisto held talks here today on bilateral and 
international issues of mutual concern. 
  During the talks, Li said the two countries have made great 
achievements in exchanges and cooperation in the economic, 
scientific and other fields and China is satisfied with the 
smooth development of Sino-Finnish relations. 
  On China's foreign policy, Li said China pursues a policy 
characterized by independence and self-reliance with peace and 
development as its goals. 
  This is the first visit to Europe ever paid by China's CPPCC 
chairman and its purpose is to deepen mutual understanding, 
expand exchanges and enhance cooperation. 
  Haavisto said China's great success in economic construction 
has won respect and admiration from the people of the world. 
  "Finland hopes to further cooperate with China in various 
fields and take an active part in China's economic 
construction," the foreign minister said. 
  He added that Li's visit will deepen China's understanding 
of 
Finland, promote the friendship between the two peoples and 
boost economic and trade relations between the two countries. 
  The two leaders also exchanged views over international 
issues of mutual concern. 
  Li arrived here Monday [2 May] and has met with Finnish 
President Martti Ahtisaari and parliament Speaker Riitta 
Uosukainen. 
  He is on an official goodwill visit to five European 
countries -- Finland, Sweden, Norway, Denmark and Belgium. 

</TEXT>

