<H3> <TI>   Chen Muhua Meets New York-Based Chinese Press </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Muhua Meets New York-Based Chinese Press </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0405005394 Beijing XINHUA in English 2249 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0405005394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, May 3 (XINHUA) -- China said here 
today that it would do its utmost to ensure the fourth world 
women's congress, to be convened in Beijing in September, a 
complete success. 
  In her meeting with the Chinese press based in New York this 
morning, Chen Muhua, president of the All-China Women's 
Federation, said that the preparation for the congress had been 
going on very well. 
  She said that she would like to extend warm welcome to all 
those who would participate in the Beijing congress on behalf of 
the host nation. 
  Chen, also a chairperson of the Standing Committee of 
China's 
National People's Congress, attended a ceremony on Monday [2 
May] to receive the Maurice Pate award conferred to her 
federation by the UN Children's Fund. 
  According to Chen, there will be about 10,000 delegates, UN 
officials and correspondents, and 20,000 representatives from 
different non-governmental organizations present on the occasion. 
  "China pays great attention to the successful convening of 
the congress," Chen said, "And its State Council has already set 
up an organizational committee, which comprises senior leaders 
from several dozens of government ministries." 
  According to sources of the United Nations, regional 
meetings, whose job it is to help finalize the draft documents 
for the world congress, will be convened in the next few months. 
  "As the host country," Chen said, "China will try to send 
delegates to these regional preparatory meetings to collect 
information and to gain a better understanding of the regional 
concerns, so as to ensure a complete success of the Beijing 
congress." 

</TEXT>

