<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing Attends Navy Anniversary Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liu Huaqing Attends Navy Anniversary Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0305160194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1533 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0305160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 3 (XINHUA) -- The departments directly 
under the Chinese People's Navy held an evening today to mark 
the 45th anniversary of the founding of the People's Navy. 
  Liu Huaqing, member of the Standing Committee of the 
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party 
of China (CPC) and vice-chairman of the Central Military 
Commission, attended the evening. 
  Also present were Chi Haotian, minister of defence; Yu 
Yongbo, director of the General Political Department of the 
People's Liberation Army (PLA); and Fu Quanyou, director of the 
General Logistics Department of PLA. 
  Before the gathering began, Vice-Chairman Liu met with Liu 
Zhiyan, a Navy soldier who was seriously injured in rescuing six 
children. He praised Liu Zhiyan's bravery and encouraged him to 
continue to serve the people. 
  Entertainment at the event included singing and dancing 
which 
depicted the development of the Chinese People's Navy under the 
leadership of the Chinese Communist Party and the three 
generations of leaders, Mao Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and Jiang 
Zemin. 

</TEXT>

