<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investment Welcomed in Fujian's Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investment Welcomed in Fujian's Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0305153494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1402 GMT 
3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0305153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, May 3 (CNS) -- Fuzhou, capital of Fujian 
Province, staged a fair on land development today offering 101 
pieces of land for development with nearly 300 domestic and 
foreign real estate businessmen attending the meeting. 
  Among the 101 pieces of land with a total area of 4600 
hectares, 61 are offered for real estate development, totaling 
300 hectares and the rest for industrial purposes and whole 
pieces of land development, totaling 4300 hectares. 
  Among those for real estate development, 15 pieces of land 
are located in urban districts of Fuzhou while most of the rest 
pieces of land in the economically developed coastal counties 
and cities. The investors are allowed to use the offered land to 
build up commercial housing, hotels and villas. Those pieces of 
land used for industrial purposes and for whole pieces of land 
development mainly located in various economic developing zones, 
and they can be used to develop hi-tec items, factory workshops 
and warehouses as well as for agricultural and processing 
industrial purposes. 
  The terms of utilization of these pieces of land are: 70 
years for residential housing; 40 years for commercial, tourism 
and entertainment purposes and 50 years for those purposes of 
industry, education, science, technology and culture as well as 
public health and sports. 

</TEXT>

