<H3> <TI>   Urumqi Music Radio Station Starts Broadcasting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urumqi Music Radio Station Starts Broadcasting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3004145694 Urumqi Xinjiang Television Network in Mandarin 
1330 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3004145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Urumqi Xinjiang Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Xinjiang News" program] </F>
  [Text] The first music radio station in China's 
northwestern region, the Xinjiang People's Radio Broadcasting 
Network's music station, formally started to broadcast yesterday 
in Urumqi. 
  Party and government leaders of the autonomous region, 
including Janabil, Amudun Niyaz, Feng Dazhen, (Paxia Yixia), and 
other comrades went to the station to extend their 
congratulations. 
  Janabil, deputy secretary of the regional party committee 
and 
chairman of the regional committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference, expressed warm 
congratulations to the station on behalf of the regional party 
committee and the regional government at a ceremony for the 
start of broadcasting by the music station. 
  Janabil said: The music station should publicize the main 
theme and adhere to the correct media orientation like the 
people's station and the economic affairs station. It should 
broadcast more musical works which can represent China's 
national tradition and spirit and the atmosphere of the times, 
as well as famous and artistic Chinese and foreign music and 
songs. The music station and the people's station should take 
an active attitude toward organizing the creation of more 
musical works which can encourage people of various 
nationalities to work hard and make progress and satisfy the 
increasing spiritual and cultural needs of the people. 
  In conclusion, Janabil expressed his hope that various 
circles in society would vigorously support the music station. 
He said that concerned departments should strengthen their 
leadership over the music station while comrades of the music 
station should work hard and find ways and means to accomplish 
the propaganda task entrusted to them by the party and the 
government. 

</TEXT>

