<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Extends Cultural Cooperation With Taiwan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Extends Cultural Cooperation With Taiwan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604065294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0640 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604065294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, April 26 (XINHUA) -- The Shanghai Shaoxing 
Opera troop will tour Taiwan next month, marking a further 
advance in cultural exchange between China's largest 
municipality and the island province. 
  Shanghai conducted 63 cultural exchange projects with Taiwan 
last year, and so far this year exchanges have included a visit 
by its symphony orchestra. 
  The 65-member opera troupe, scheduled to leave Shanghai for 
Taiwan May 2, includes noted performers Yuan Xuefen, Xu Yulan 
and Wang Wenjuan. 
  The troupe will perform traditional operas including "A 
dream 
of Red Mansions", "The Western Chamber", "Meng Lijun" and "Liang 
Shanbo and Zhu Yingtai". 

