<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   CNA Reports Li Itinerary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CNA Reports Li Itinerary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704143294 Taipei CNA in English 1307 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Flor Wang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, April 27 (CNA) -- The Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs Wednesday [27 April] formally announced the itinerary 
for President Li Teng-hui's trip to Central America and Africa. 
  Li will first head to Managua, Nicaragua next Wednesday on 
board a China Airlines chartered flight. He will then visit 
Costa Rica and South Africa, where he has been invited to attend 
presidential inauguration ceremonies on May 6 and May 8, 
respectively. 
  Prior to his return to Taipei on May 15, Li will also visit 
Swaziland on May 12, the Foreign Affairs Ministry reported. 
  Li will seek to strengthen and consolidate cooperative ties 
and friendly relationships with the four countries, Presidential 
Spokesman Raymond Tai said. 
  He said the trip is part of the Republic of China [ROC]'s 
strategy to play a more active role in the international 
community -- a policy it is pursuing as payback for the help it 
received from other countries during its own course of 
development. 

</TEXT>

