<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guizhou Province To Develop Coal Resources </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guizhou Province To Develop Coal Resources </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0105070894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0503 GMT 
30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0105070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guiyang, April 30 (CNS) -- China will develop its 
coal resources in Guizhou Province in the not-far-distant future 
in order to alleviate the pressures on coal transportation from 
the north to the south and to supply energy to the southeast 
coastal regions. 
  The development of coal resources in Guizhou would form a 
rational distribution of energy in the country. It is estimated 
that Guizhou's coal reserves rank third in the country and more 
than the total coal resources in ten or more of the southern 
provinces. 
  Guizhou's coal industry has been speeded up in recent years 
with newly-built and renovated projects going into production 
this year and next year and a batch of large-scale coal mines 
with a yearly output of three to four million tonnes will be 
built. Some power plants in coal mining areas will be built to 
realize the conversion of coal into electric power. 
  Experts from the State Planning Commission and the Ministry 
of Coal Industry have concluded, however, after a joint 
investigation into Guizhou's coal resources that coal 
development in Guizhou was impractical and failed to meet the 
demand for quality anthracite and coking coal in the south. 
Guizhou, in response, decided to jointly develop its coal 
resources with relevant departments and other provinces short of 
coal as well as with foreign investors to speed up the 
development of the coal industry there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

