<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   China, Portugal To Increase Scientific Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    China, Portugal To Increase Scientific Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3004033694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0211 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3004033694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lisbon, April 29 (XINHUA) -- A Sino-Portuguese 
committee on science and technology met here today and signed an 
agreement to implement the cooperation accord reached between 
the two countries last year. 
  According to the summary of the meeting, China and Portugal 
will launch exchanges and cooperation on 20 projects in such 
fields as biological technology, material science, agriculture, 
and environmental protection. 
  During the meeting, each side briefed the other on the 
policy 
of their country regarding the development of science and 
technology and expressed a desire for further cooperation. 

</TEXT>

